            <title>[SPR-6369] Support for &apos;groups&apos; in addition to @Valid for @MVC Controllers</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6369</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I want to be able to specify the JSR303 validation group when specifying @Valid in @Controller-s.&lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t want the validation to be run against the default group every time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess currently I can inject a javax.validation.Validator reference in the @Controller and handle this programmatically. Would be nice if this can be driven through an annotation as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But @Valid doesn&apos;t support a &quot;group&quot; attribute though.&lt;br/&gt;
What do you guys think?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
